cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on optimizing network capacity and QoS through traffic offloading schemes in a heterogeneous cellular network architecture. 
2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper proposes joint optimization of user associations, ON-OFF states of SBSs, and power control, which can be viewed as a game-theoretic problem. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers the operating characteristics of SBSs with different power sources and proposes a two-stage energy-aware traffic offloading scheme, which involves system modeling and control. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses statistical information of energy arrival and traffic load to optimize the energy-aware traffic offloading schemes, which can be viewed as an information-theoretic problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers the QoS requirement in the traffic offloading schemes, which is related to multimedia applications.
